cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.MA, cs.DS, cs.NE 

The paper deals with sensor fault detection using group testing and Kalman filtering. This involves concepts from systems and control theory (cs.SY), information theory (cs.IT), and mathematical analysis (cs.MA). The use of Bayesian inference in the adaptive group testing method also suggests a connection to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
